<p>Can you share the rest of your code (ideally as a github link) and the actual error message(s) you’re seeing?</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-01-16T15:04:38.887Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":1,"reads":289,"readers_count":288,"score":67.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":450389,"topic_slug":"using-neo-vortex-integrated-encoder","display_username":"Fletch","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":9105,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades"},"post_url":"/t/using-neo-vortex-integrated-encoder/450389/2","custom_user_title":"3181/3015 Mentor | 213/1373 Alum | CSA/FTAA/Jack-of-all-Trades","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3286106,"name":null,"username":"heightsbytes","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/h/ac91a4/{size}.png","created_at":"2024-01-16T20:34:25.655Z","cooked":"<p>Unfortunately, I do not have access to the motors for a little bit to get the exact error message.</p>
<p>I just opened a timed robot base and just added the two lines below, nothing else. The goal was to simply test an intake prototype and get some encoder reading, unfortunately this wasn’t possible due to the aforementioned error.</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">  rev::CANSparkFlex m_intake{1, rev::CANSparkFlex::MotorType::kBrushless};
  rev::SparkRelativeEncoder m_intakeEncoder = 
        m_intake.GetEncoder(rev::SparkRelativeEncoder::Type::kHallSensor, 7168);
</code></pre>
<p>As far as I know, the Spark Flex is updated to the latest version. We flashed it just before using it with the latest version.</p>","post_number":3,"post_type":1,"posts_count":10,"updated_at":"2024-01-16T20:34:25.655Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":2,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":240,"readers_count":239,"score":68.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":450389,"topic_slug":"using-neo-vortex-integrated-encoder","display_username":null,"primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":null,"reply_to_user":{"id":9105,"username":"Fletch1373","name":"Fletch","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/fletch1373/{size}/220073_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":61289,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/using-neo-vortex-integrated-encoder/450389/3","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3286117,"name":"Will Toth","username":"Will_Toth","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/will_toth/{size}/111117_2.png","created_at":"2024-01-16T20:42:10.513Z","cooked":"<p>The sensor in the Flex is not a hall sensor. Just do this:</p>
